# .cursorrules

## Project: Marugen Koi & Arowana Farm — Business Management App
## Language: Myanmar (Burmese) & English bilingual support
## Stack: React 19 + Vite 8 + Tailwind CSS v4 + Supabase + Gemini API

## Tech Rules
- Always use React functional components with hooks (ErrorBoundary is the only class component)
- Use Tailwind CSS for all styling (dark theme: bg-slate-900/800/700)
- Primary color palette: slate + cyan (text-cyan-400, bg-cyan-500)
- Use lucide-react for all icons
- State management: lifted React state in App.jsx (useState) + src/lib/database.js for cloud sync — no Redux
- React 19: no 'use client' directive needed in this Vite SPA
- React 19: use createRoot() from react-dom/client — never ReactDOM.render()
- React 19: Strict Mode runs effects twice in dev (normal)
- All forms: controlled components (useState)
- API calls: async/await with try/catch
- Avoid class components — ErrorBoundary is the only exception
- TypeScript not required — plain JSX only

## Code Style
- Component props destructured in function signature
- Event handlers named: handleXxx or onXxx
- Constants UPPERCASE in constants.js
- Custom hooks in /hooks/ folder, prefixed "use"
- All monetary values: formatSGD() helper (S$XX.XX)
- Dates: date-fns library, format("dd MMM yyyy")

## Business Domain Knowledge
- Fish types: Koi (Kohaku, Sanke, Showa, Kinginrin, Ogon),
  Arowana (Super Red, Cross Back Golden, Malaysian Golden, Silver)
- Singapore delivery areas: 25 HDB towns
- Customer tiers: Bronze, Silver, Gold, Platinum
- Product categories: Fish Food, Water Treatment, Equipment,
  Accessories, Medicine, Pond Supplies
- Expense categories: Feed, Transport, Utilities, Rent,
  Equipment, Labor, Medicine, Packaging, Marketing
- Currency: Singapore Dollar (SGD, S$)
- Invoice IDs: INV-XXXXX format
- Delivery IDs: DEL-XXXXX format

## AI Chat Agent
- Model: gemini-2.5-flash (Google Gemini API)
- Bilingual: Myanmar + English
- System prompt must include current business data counts
- Max tokens: 1000
- API key: VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY in .env

## Component Patterns
- Modal: always check if open prop before rendering
- Tables: overflow-x-auto wrapper
- Forms: validation before submit
- Loading states: spinner or skeleton
- Empty states: helpful message + action button

## File Structure
- One component per file
- Module files in /modules/ (Dashboard, Inventory, etc.)
- Reusable UI in /components/ui/
- No inline styles — Tailwind only
- No CSS files except index.css (Tailwind import only)
